Name.creator: Gill, Eric, 1882-1940
Description.note: One of two gridded drawings of a hand holding a tool, perhaps a chisel.  The same drawings are traced on the reverse, with text in Gill’s hand explaining how the tool is used.
Title: Untitled

Name.creator: Gill, Eric, 1882-1940
Description.note: A note in the box states that these drawings are, “A collection of pages from a sketch book used by my Father Eric Gill in Paris, Joanna Hague (nee Gill).” The drawings consist of 12 nudes drawn from life, some dated August 29, 1938.
Format.dimensions: 8.5 x 10 drawings in a 9 x 11.5 inches case
Title: Paris sketchbook
